                          Call for Papers - BDMICS 2018 -


3rd International Workshop on Big Data Management in Cloud Systems 
(BDMICS 2018)
In parallel with DEXA 2018 (www.dexa.org)

September 4, 2018, Regensburg, Germany
Workshop URL: http://www.dexa.org *or* http://www.irit.fr/BDMICS2018

1. Important Dates:

Manuscript submissions: May 14th, 2018
Notification of acceptance: June 15th, 2018
Final version deadline: June 25th, 2018

2. Publication

A. Proceedings
All accepted papers will be published by *IEEE Computer Society*'s 
Conference Publishing Services (CPS) as proceedings of the
DEXA'17 workshops (indexed by the Thomson ISI Web of Knowledge). At 
least one author is required to attend the workshop and
present the paper.

B. Distinguished Papers

Extended versions of selected papers will be published in the 
International Journal "Transactions on Large-scale Data and
Knowledge-Centerd Systems", LNCS Springer Verlag ( 
http://tldks.faw.at/home/)

3. Scope & Topics

Big data management in large-scale distributed systems and new 
applications that require voluminous, distributed, heterogeneous and
  dynamic data is the subject of many research. These research leaded, 
principally, in Cloud  computing topics will make considerable
  impact on the viability of the next generation of large-scale data 
management systems for big data applications.
Today, these topics require more research in order to raise still open 
challenges like scalability, elasticity, consistency,
security and autonomic data management.

The main objective of the annual international workshop on Big Data 
Management in Cloud Systems is to present and exchange
the latest results in research and applications,  and to shape future 
directions.

Original papers preferably but not limited to the following topics are 
welcome :

     * Big Data Science and Foundation
     * Big Data Infrastructures
     * Big Data Mining and Analytics
     * Big Data and Semantic Web
     * Data Storage and Management
     * Data Integration and Metadata Management
     * Data Stream Systems
     * Query Languages
     * Dynamic Data Placement Issues
     * Flexible and Adaptive Query Processing
     * Support for Scalable and Elastic Services
     * Query Processing and Optimization
     * Big Data Warehousing
     * Cost Models in Heterogeneous Environments
     * Economic Pricing Models
     * Dynamic Resource Management, Reservation, and Scheduling
     * Multi-tenancy and Workload Isolation
     * Locating Data Sources/Resources and Scalability
     * Web Services
     * Workload Adaptability in Heterogeneous Environments
     * Transaction Management
     * Replicated Copy Control and Caching
     * Big Data Privacy and Security
     * Big Data Visualization
     * Big Data Applications for Vertical Industries
     * Mobile Cloud Computing
     * Large-scale Distributed Applications and Experiences
     * Performance Evaluation and Benchmarking

Workshop Program Chairperson

Abdelkader Hameurlain, IRIT, Paul Sabatier University, Toulouse, France

Program Committee

Reza Akbarinia, INRIA & LIRMM , University of Montpellier, France
Djamal Benslimane, LIRIS,  Universty of Lyon, France
Shahram Ghandeharizadeh, University of Southern California, Los Angeles, USA
Tasos Gounaris, Aristotle University of Thessaloniki, Greece
Omar Khadeer Hussain, University of New South Wales Canberra, Canberra, 
Australia
Maria Indrawan-Santiago, Faculty of Information Technology Monash 
University, Melbourne, Australia
Sergio Ilarri, University of Zaragoza, Spain
Harald Kosch, University of Passau, Germany
Kjetil Norvag, Norwegian University of Science and Technology,Trondheim, 
Norway
Philippe Lamarre, LIRIS, INSA of Lyon, France
Carlos Ordonez, University of Houston, USA
Claudia Roncancio, LIG, Grenoble, France
Viera Rozinajova, Slovak University of Technology, Bratislava, Slovak 
Republic
Soror Sahri, LIPADE, Descartes Paris University, France
Hala Skaf-Molli, LINA, Nantes University, France
Joseph G. Vella, Computer Information Systems, University of Malta, Malta
Shaoyi Yin, IRIT, Paul Sabatier University, Toulouse, France


4. Submission Details

Authors are invited to submit original, unpublished research papers in 
English, which are not being considered in another forum.
Papers should be no longer than 5 pages (two-columns, A4), including 
figures and references, and should be formatted according
to the IEEE format: 
http://www.ieee.org/conferences_events/conferences/publishing/templates.html 


Submission of papers (in PDF format) is made electronically through the 
main conference management system ConfDriver: 
http://confdriver.ifs.tuwien.ac.at/dexa2018 (Workshop BDMICS'18)

Submitted papers will be peer-reviewed by at least 3 reviewers. Papers 
will be carefully evaluated based on originality,
significance, technical soundness, and clarity of exposition.
